Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Renovations Completed: New lobbies, conference center and tenant lounge, refreshed restrooms, new entry doors, enhanced wayfinding and exterior signage, new exterior building lighting and enhanced parking structure aesthetics. Mission Ridge is a 2-building Class A office campus in Mission Viejo, California. Mission Viejo is conveniently located between San Diego and Los Angeles counties, adjacent to both I-5 and SR241 (Foothill Toll Road). Mission Viejo is a business-friendly city devoted to helping businesses grow and succeed, increasing the job base for residents, and improving the economic well-being and quality of life for all. Mission Viejo is one of the safest cities in California and it is consistently ranked as one of the top 15 cities in the nation, earning a reputation as one of the best places in the region to work, live, and play. Mission Ridge is ideally located and perfect for auto-commuters with a 3-minute drive to the on- and off-ramps of I-5, 10-minutes to I-405, and ample surface and covered parking with an electronic car charging stations. Within a 1-minute drive or 10-minute walk of Mission Ridge are multiple shopping, dining, and entertainment options. The Puerta Real Shopping Center is adjacent to the Mission Ridge parking lot and includes Target, Costello's Neighborhood Tavern, and Bank of America. Kaleidoscope Courtyards is at the corner of Puerto Real and Crown Valley Parkway and is home to the Regal Edwards Cinema, LA Fitness, and Union Market which includes an array of dining and shopping options. Lastly, the well-known Shops at Mission Viejo is located across from the Kaleidoscope Courtyards and Union Market with national brands like Ann Taylor LOFT, Nordstrom, Macy's, Cheesecake Factory, and Ruby's Diner.  Mission Ridge is also a 10-minute walk or 1-minute drive to the region's only trauma center, St. Joseph Health Mission Hospital Campus, which offers one of the most comprehensive arrays of services and programs in Orange County. Mission Ridge has beautifully landscaped grounds with shaded, outdoor seating, picnic areas, fountains, and putting greens. Tenants enjoy features like fiber-optic capability with conduit inter-connectivity between buildings, a Fitness Center with shower facilities, and a mail room with FedEx drop boxes. Mission Ridge is ideal for corporate headquarters or regional offices with full floor availability and over 1,000 feet of frontage along the I-5 freeway.
